at home and a military action is under way abroad. But when the
Federal Reserve meets to consider interest rate policy on Tuesday,
it will face an economic outlook that, while complex and a bit
confusing, is more stable than it has been for months. By Richard
W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   VENEZUELA-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ A special Christmas campaign,
aimed squarely at what an executive calls ``the hearts and minds''
of Venezuela's 22 million people, is one sign of how intensely
Coca-Cola Co. is battling for the soft-drink market in Venezuela,
which for 50 years was one of the few places in the world where its
rival, Pepsico Inc., held an overwhelming lead over Coke. By
