<P>
   &UR; AMERICA'S FIRST CHRISTMAS CARD &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (900 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By PETER F. STEVENS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Did you even wonder, as your holiday greeting cards pile up, who
originated the idea that has turned into a megaindustry? Here's the
story of how in 1851 Richard H. Pease, an Albany, N.Y., shopkeeper
and skilled lithographer, decided to promote his shop with an
elaborately drawn holiday card. With superb photo of first card.
(slugged: BC-FIRST-XMAS-CARD-(HOLIDAYS)-ART-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE ORIGINS OF OUR CHRISTMAS CUSTOMS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (900 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By HAL MALEHORN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Until the latter half of the 19th century, Christmas was no big
deal for most Americans, especially rural dwellers. In fact, the
more religious citizens condemned it as a pagan holiday. Malehorn
goes on to describe how the Christmas tree, Santa Claus and
exchange of holiday cards began to take hold in America. With photo
of first Christmas card. (slugged:
BC-HOW-XMAS-EVOLVED-(HOLIDAYS)-ART-NYTSF, priority code r, category
code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TOP PICKS IN CHILDREN'S SOFTWARE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,500 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By ANN ORR &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The children's software market continues to explode, so it's
hard for parents to choose from the mindboggling array of products.
Orr, an editor at Children's Software Revue, sifts out the best
software for different age groups. An essential buying guide for
the holiday season.
</P>
<P>
   (slugged: BC-SOFTWARE-GIFTS-FOR-KIDS-(HOLIDAYS)-ART-NYTSF,
priority code r, category code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCRAPBOOKS: HOLIDAY GIFTS THAT WILL BE FAMILY TREASURES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,100 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By KATHY SENA &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Scrapbooking parties _ which turn family snapshots into family
heirlooms with a little bit of effort and imagination _ have become
the quilting bee of the '90s. And what better holiday gift than a
specially designed photo album? Sena gives simple instructions for
beginners to join the craze that is sweeping the nation. With great
art.
</P>
<P>
   (slugged: BC-CREATING-SCRAPBOOKS-(HOLIDAYS)-ART-NYTSF, priority
code r, category code l)
</P>
