leader of a wandering tribe or several people who came together in
one character, he occupies a unique place in human history and must
be regarded as a genius who saw far beyond the accepted beliefs of
his own time.
</P>
<P>
   Through the years, tales once regarded as pure myth _ King
Arthur, the Trojan War _ have come to be regarded as having a basis
in fact. So is there a chance that historical evidence of Moses
will be found?
</P>
<P>
   Briscoe sees the faint possibility that something may be
discovered in the family tomb of Rameses II, currently under
excavation. A single word, a hieroglyph chipped on a stone in
Egypt, could place Moses squarely within the framework of history.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
