   &UR; IRAQ &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-RDP (Washington) _ American and British forces launched a
third wave of air strikes on Iraqi military installations Friday
amid signs that the United States is encouraging Iraqi soldiers and
their commanders to rise up and overthrow President Saddam Hussein.
Ledeall. By Philip Shenon. With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-MILITARY (Washington) _ As American and British forces
struck targets across Iraq for a third day Friday, senior defense
officials conceded that the Pentagon has prepared a sharp, swift
attack that would end once the missiles and jets hit a ``specific
target list'' _ no sooner and no later. By Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
