Communist Party members in the Great Hall of the People, President
Jiang Zemin made clear Friday that China's economic reforms were
not a prelude to Western-style multiparty democracy and that those
who challenged the party's supremacy would be quashed.'' By
Elisabeth Rosenthal.
</P>
