<P>
   BOXER-IMPEACH (Washington) _ Sen. Barbara Boxer, D-Calif., holds
out the possibility that the Senate will not put President Clinton
on trial if the House impeaches him. She says no rule compels the
Senate to conduct a trial. It could come up with a penalty, such as
censure, short of removal from office, she says. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
