   CALIFORNIA -- CRIME. Behind a federal commission's new
recommendation that the Ninth U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals be
restructured lies a concern over crime. Or rather, how the
explosion of crime-related cases has caused the nation's largest
circuit court, which encompasses 14 million square miles in nine
states, to require division into three sub-circuits. Stricherz
