<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GASOUTH _ CHATTANOOGA _ Georgia Southern was the team of the
1980s in Division I-AA football, winning four national titles in
the decade. Now, the Eagles are on the brink of winning their fifth
title as they face Massachusetts today in the championship game in
Chattanooga. For a program that appeared to hit rock bottom with a
4-7 record in 1996, Georgia Southern is only one victory away from
another national title -- and the beginning of talk of another
dynasty. Several top players, including 2,000 yard rusher Adrian
Peterson, are underclassmen and the Eagles could contend for
several national titles during the next few years. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GASOUTH-CAPSULE _ CHATTANOOGA _ Georgia Southern-UMass
capsule. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   BKC-DELTACLASSIC _ Defending national champion Kentucky heads a
talented four-team field that will compete in the Delta Air Lines
Classic college basketball doubleheader at the Georgia Dome. The
Wildcats, who have won two NCAA titles in the last three years,
will meet Georgia Tech in the second game while Georgia faces
Fresno State in the opener. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
