<SLUG> BC-CARS-GLANCE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
1999 MERCEDES-BENZ E320 ALL-WHEEL-DRIVE WAGON
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   At A Glance:
</P>
<P>
   The Package: Luxury, midsize, five-door, seven-passenger, V-6
powered, all-wheel-drive station wagon, which debuted in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: True Mercedes sedanlike ride and handling; powerful
and smooth engine; roomy for a midsize vehicle; lots of safety and
luxury features.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Way overpriced in comparison with some of the
high-end sport-utility vehicles that offer more space and greater
versatility.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Volvo V70 and V90 wagons, as well as the
Lexus LX 470/Toyota Land Cruiser and Range Rover sport-utility
vehicles.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: 20 miles per gallon city, 26 highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $49,990 plus $595 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $54,935, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-minus.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
