<SLUG> BC-COXCOMM19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cox Communications hires BBDO ad agency
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Cox Communications has hired the local office of BBDO
to develop a new ad campaign to promote itself as a provider of all
kinds of new digital communication services.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta-based company expects to spend $3 million annually
with BBDO South, which had $247.5 million in billings last year.
The Cox Communications account represents the fifth new client BBDO
South has signed in 1998, the company said.
</P>
<P>
   BBDO beat out 17 other ad agencies nationwide. It was selected
for its ``strategic consumer insight and outstanding creative
work,'' said Virginia Gray, Cox Communications' vice president of
marketing.
</P>
<P>
   The change in agencies comes at an important time for Cox
Communications. It has been expanding beyond the company's
traditional cable TV business.
</P>
<P>
   In systems spread from coast to coast, the company has been
increasingly offering telephone service and high-speed access to
the Internet through its new digital network.
</P>
<P>
   The company ultimately wants to become a general provider of
communications services, offering customers one-stop shopping for
cable TV, telephone and Internet service.
</P>
<P>
   Such a strategy requires a new brand identity, the company
believes. Right now, few of its 3.8 million customers know Cox
Communications offers more than cable TV.
</P>
<P>
   Cox Communications executives say they are looking for an ad
campaign that does two things. First, the company wants a
consistent look and feel for the branding of its growing roster of
products.
</P>
<P>
   Second, it wants people to begin seeing the company not as a
cable system but as a new breed of communications company that
offers all kinds of reliable services.
</P>
<P>
   For their part, BBDO executives say they share Cox
Communications' world view. ``We've seen the future, and the future
is digital,'' says Chris Hall, chief executive of BBDO South.
</P>
<P>
   BBDO South is a unit of BBDO Worldwide. Its clients include
Georgia-Pacific, Lenox Square and Phipps Plaza, and the U.S.
Department of Housing and Urban Development.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
