</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IMPEACH-FBN-JETS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IMPEACHMENT PROCEEDINGS COULD INTERRUPT JETS-BILLS GAME 
</HEADLINE>
  (See also IMPEACH, IMPEACH-POLL, IMPEACH-ASSESS, IMPEACH-SCENE,
IMPEACH-DEBATERS, IMPEACH-RULES, IMPEACH-CLINTON,
IMPEACH-LIVINGSTON, IMPEACH-SENATE, IMPEACH-VOICES, IMPEACH-TV,
IMPEACH-TV-NOTEBOOK.) (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Viewers of Saturday's crucial Jets-Bills game at
12:30 p.m. ET on Channel 2 in New York could experience
interruptions from CBS News' coverage of the impeachment vote in
the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
   After debate Friday, the House session was expected to reconvene
at 9 a.m. Saturday. Further debate is expected to take an hour,
followed by votes on each of the four articles of impeachment. Each
vote is expected to take 15 to 20 minutes, said Sandy Genelius, a
CBS News spokeswoman. If the schedule holds, the votes will be over
around 11:30, and the game will not be interrupted.
</P>
<P>
   If the debate and votes stretch beyond 12:30, Genelius said,
``we will cover the votes.'' She declined to say whether CBS would
leave the game, or carry it simultaneously on a split screen with
the House votes. ``There are a variety of options, and we'll decide
when the situation arises,'' Genelius said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
