   IMPEACH-SENATE (Undated) _ With the impeachment process all but
certain to move to the next phase, the Senate is reluctantly
preparing to take up the task of serving as President Clinton's
jury, hoping it can rise above the bare-knuckles partisanship of
the House, according to Northwest senators.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``w'' category.)
</P>
