   (NYT23) WASHINGTON -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- IMPEACH-4, 12-18 -- On
the subway to the U.S. Capitol building, Alcee Hastings, left,
D-Fla., and Abbe Lowell, the House Judiciary Committee's Democratic
counsel, look over paper work Friday. During House debates on
articles of impeachment, Democrats insisted that Americans were
witnessing a political coup. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
