<P>
   BIZ-PROFILE-TRUDELL (subsked) (Detroit) _ Profile of Cynthia
Mary Trudell of GM, who would become the first woman to run a car
division for an American or foreign auto maker. By Keith Bradsher.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BRIEFS (Undated) _ A weekly column of short items on people
and personalities that make business more than a dollars-and-cents
proposition. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-COMMERCIAL-FINANCIAL (Tulsa, Okla.) _ Commercial Financial
grew like a miracle: a collection agency that bought banks'
written-off credit card accounts, milked amazing revenue from them,
and sold them in securitized form to the investing public. Then a
scandal erupted involving possible insider dealings and earnings
inflation. When the company's own credit line was cut off, it found
itself in the supremely ironic position of using a Chapter 11
filing to stave off paying its bills. By Carol Marie Cropper.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   ETHICS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Right Thing column: When the boss
lies in public, or even under oath, what happens to the integrity
of the rank and file? By Jeffrey L. Seglin. (Moved).
