   (NYT17) WASHINGTON -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- IMPEACH-3, 12-18 --
Visitors to the U.S. Capitol wait on line for a tour in Statuary
Hall on Friday. The House, meeting on the floor directly above the
waiting tourists, was debating articles of impeachment against
President Clinton. A vote on the articles is expected Saturday.
(Justin Lane/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) UNDATED -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- IRAQ-BOMBER, 12-18 -- After
three decades of controversy and ridicule, $30 billion and a string
of mishaps, one of the nation's most costly and troubled combat
aircraft, the B-1 bomber (similar to the one seen in this undated
photo), flew into combat for the very first time, the Pentagon
announced Friday. The bombers joined in the second day of attacks
against Iraq on Thursday, striking a military complex near Baghdad.
(Boeing/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) JERUSALEM -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- IRAQ-RDP, 12-18 -- Netanel
Simantov,10, of Long Island, N.Y., is aided in an attempt to don a
gas mask Friday. Israeli authorities set up stalls in the streets
of the capital to provide instruction in the use of gas masks for
those who fear that Iraq - now experiencing its third day of
airstrikes by U.S. and British forces - will retaliate by firing
missiles carrying chemical or biological warheads toward Israel.
(Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) ABERDEEN, Wash. -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC.
20 -- SENIORS-ELECTRONIC-INVEST-3, 12-18 -- David L. Woodland likes
the freedom of doing on-line trading whenever he wants. ``I'm not
in the insurance business anymore,'' he says. ``I'm in the
investing business.'' (Duncan Livingston/New York Times Photo)
*LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN.,
DEC. 20 -- SENIORS-ELECTRONIC-INVEST-2, 12-18 -- Carol Potts, a
crafts designer whose works include glass frames, says she does not
need a financial adviser. ``I'm very analytical, and I like to get
involved in research,'' she says. (Kim Kulish/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN.,
