Oval Office on Friday. White House officials said that, despite the
impeachment debate underway in the House, Clinton was in a good
mood Friday. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) NEW YORK -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 20 --
QUENTIN-CRISP-PROFILE, 12-18 -- Quentin Crisp, with Amanda LaPore
during a party celebrating Crisp's life as a performer, humorist
and unapologetically flamboyant homosexual. Crisp, who turns 90 on
Christmas Day, first achieved notoriety in 1958 with the
publication of ``The Naked Civil Servant,'' a memoir of his
travails as a gay misfit. (Miles Ladin/New York Times Photo) *LITE
