Wyckoff Jr., John D. Spears, Christopher H. Browne and William H.
Browne. Not pictured is Thomas H. Shrager. (Barbara Alper/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) PALM BEACH, Fla. -- Dec. 18, 1998 -- PRETTY-PLATES-3-COX,
12-18 -- A woven tri color pasta and fish dish by Gerard Reuther,
chef at Janiero in Palm Beach. It's more than an artful twist -
there's psychology behind placing and choosing foods to go
together. ``You want to have lots of contrasts, textures, busy
things going on for the eye to enjoy,'' says Reuther. (Sherman
Zent/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) PALM BEACH GARDENS, Fla. -- Dec. 18, 1998 --
PRETTY-PLATES-2-COX, 12-18 -- Baked apple by Colin O'Daly, chef at
Roly's Bistro in Palm Beach Gardens. ``You see it in your mind's
eye first, and you can tell whether it's right or not,'' says
O'Daly, who likens plate design to meditation. (Sherman Zent/Cox
News Service Photo)
