NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, DECEMBER 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-FREUD-GAYS-NYT (moved on Friday, Dec. 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Dec. 11,
about psychoanalysts and homosexuality misstated a credential of
Dr. Richard C. Friedman, a New York analyst. He is the author of
``Male Homosexuality: A Contemporary Psychoanalytic Perspective,''
not a co-author. The article also misstated the book's publication
date. It was 1988; a paperback edition was published in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   BC-IMMIG-DEPORTATIONS-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 14,
about the deportation of immigrants from the United States
misstated the period in which 106,000 immigrants with criminal
convictions were deported. It was 1997 and 1998, not 1998 alone. As
the article said, the figure represented a 52 percent increase from
the previous two years.
</P>
